INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (197,2,'2013-10-01 16:48:58','2013-10-01 16:48:58','<h2>Registration</h2> \r\n<a href=\"#login-before-register\" alt=\"Login Before you register\" title=\"Login Before you register\">Why do I need to login before I register?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#login-with-kimbia\" alt=\"Where is login for Long Island and Dallas\" title=\"Where is login for Long Island and Dallas\">I\'m trying to register for the Long Island Brain Tumor Walk or the Nashville Brain Tumor Race, but I can\'t find my login. Where did it go?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#registration-fee\" alt=\"Regsitration Fee\" title=\"Regsitration Fee\">Is there a registration fee?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#fundraise-minimum\" alt=\"Fundraise Minimum\" title=\"Fundraise Minimum\">Am I required to fundraise a minimum amount? </a>\r\n<a href=\"#event-t-shirt\" alt=\"Event t-shirts\" title=\"Event t-shirts\">Will I receive an event t-shirt?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#register-offline\" alt=\"Register-offline\" title=\"Register-offline\">I can\'t register online. Is there another way to register?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#register-children\" alt=\"register children\" title=\"register children\">Do I need to register my children? </a>\r\n<!--<a href=\"#pre-register-online\" alt=\"pre-register online\" title=\"pre-register online\">Why should I pre-register online?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#reg-forms\" alt=\"Downloadable Registration Form\" title=\"Downloadable Registration Form\">Downloadable Registration Form</a><!-- -->\r\n\r\n<h2>Donations</h2>\r\n<a href=\"#funds\" alt=\"funds\" title=\"funds\">Where do Brain Tumor Events funds go?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#checks\" alt=\"checks\" title=\"checks\">To whom do I make checks payable?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#matching-gifts\" alt=\"matching gifts\" title=\"matching gifts\">What are Matching Gift Programs?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#tax-id\" alt=\"tax id\" title=\"tax id\">What is the tax ID number for National Brain Tumor Society?</a>\r\n<h2>Day of Event</h2> \r\n<a href=\"#pets\" alt=\"pets\" title=\"pets\">Are pets allowed at the event?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#stroller\" alt=\"pets\" title=\"pets\">Can I bring a stroller?</a>\r\n<a href=\"#emergency-management\" alt=\"emergency management\" title=\"emergency management\">What emergency management procedures are in place for the event?</a>\r\n<h2>Contact Us</h2>\r\nIf you have a question we haven’t answered here, please <a href=\"/contact-us/\" alt=\"contact us\" title=\"contact us\">contact us</a>!\r\n<h2>Registration</h2>\r\n<h4 id=\"login-before-register\" alt=\"login before register\" title=\"login before register\">Why do I need to login before I register?</h4>\r\n\r\nAll event participants with an existing user account will save time with registration, by logging into their accounts first. As an existing user, the system will remember your contact information and automatically fill out most of the registration form for you. In addition, you will gain access to your Participant Center address book and any updates you made to your previous personal fundraising page(s).\r\n\r\nIf you received an email from National Brain Tumor Society with your username and password or if you previously participated in one of our events, you will be recognized by the online registration system as an existing user account. If you already have a user account and attempt to register without logging in, you may receive a system error or incomplete registration.\r\n\r\nYou can always <a href=\"http://www.braintumorcommunity.org/site/UserLogin\" target=\"_blank\" alt=\"user login\" title=\"user login\">lookup</a> your username or password, and request it be emailed to you. Once you are registered for the event, you will be able to edit your username and password.\r\n\r\nHave questions? Contact us at <a href=\"mailto:events@braintumor.org\">events@braintumor.org</a>.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"login-with-kimbia\" alt=\"Where is login for Long Island and Dallas\" title=\"Where is login for Long Island and Dallas\">I\'m trying to register for the Long Island Brain Tumor Walk or the Nashville Brain Tumor Race, but I can\'t find my login. Where did it go?</h4>\r\n\r\nThe Long Island and Nashville events do not require a login. Once you register, you will be emailed a unique web link that will direct you to your Personal Page. \r\n\r\nHave questions? Contact us at <a href=\"mailto:events@braintumor.org\">events@braintumor.org</a>.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"registration-fee\">Is there a registration fee?</h4>\r\n\r\nThere are no registration fees for a Brain Tumor Walk. However, you are required to register in order to participate in the walk and gain access to all event activities. Fees are required for any timed event such as the Race for Hope - Philadelphia and the Charlotte Brain Tumor Race. $35/$10 prior to online registration closing - $50/$15 thereafter. Fees for the Boston Brain Tumor Ride are $25/$10 prior to online registration closing - $50/$35 thereafter. \r\n\r\nUpon registration, you will receive a personal fundraising page and useful online tools to help you jumpstart your efforts. Even after the event is over, you will still have access to your personal fundraising page, allowing you to maximize your impact in the fight against brain tumors.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"fundraise-minimum\">Am I required to fundraise a minimum amount? </h4>\r\n\r\nAdult walkers/runners are encouraged to raise a minimum of $200 or more to help fund the discovery of a cure and better treatments for brain tumors.\r\n\r\nAdult participants in the Boston Brain Tumor Ride are required to raise $500 and youth are required to raise $100 up to 2 months post event. More details can be found on the event website. \r\n\r\n**Are you participating in the Pan Mass Challenge? Send us your PMC registration form and your fundraising dollars are reduced to $250.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"event-t-shirt\">Will I receive an event t-shirt?</h4>\r\n\r\nTo maximize every dollar raised, we only provide event T-shirts to registered survivors and volunteers. All Boston Ride participants that raise $500 will receive a Boston Brain Tumor Ride shirt. \r\n\r\nNational Brain Tumor Society T-shirts for adults and children are available at each event, in exchange for a donation.\r\n\r\n<!--<h4 id=\"pre-register-online\">Why should I pre-register online?</h4>\r\nWhen you pre-register online, you will gain access to an array of online tools through your own personal fundraising page. Pre-registering also allows you extra time to fundraise and spread awareness about brain tumors. \r\n\r\nIf you would prefer to register by mail, please complete and return this <a href=\"http://www.braintumorcommunity.org/site/DocServer/?docID=8682\" target=\"_blank\" alt=\"downloadable registration form\" title=\"downloadable registration form\">downloadable registration form</a>.\r\n<!-- -->\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"register-offline\">I can\'t register online. Is there another way to register?</h4>\r\n\r\nIf you can\'t register online, you can use the appropriate offline registration form.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/BTW_14_RegForm_Final.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Brain Tumor Walk</strong></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/BTWR_14_RegForm_Final.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Brain Tumor Race</strong></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/BTR_14_RegForm_Final.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Brain Tumor Ride</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"register-children\">Do I need to register my children? </h4>\r\n\r\nChildren ages 6-17 are required to register. Children ages 5 and under do not need to register for this event.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"walk-and-volunteer\">Can I participate and volunteer?</h4>\r\n\r\nYes! If you plan to participate and volunteer, please register as a Participant FIRST, and then <a href=\"/contact-us/\" alt=\"contact us\" title=\"contact us\">email your contact information to us</a>.\r\n\r\n<i>Please note, Volunteers are not automatically considered registered participants unless they complete the process above.</i>\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"mailing-address\">When I register for the first time, should I use my home or work mailing address?</h4>\r\n\r\nParticipants should register using their home mailing address. This helps to eliminate confusion at registration and the chance of duplicate mailings.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"individual-and-team\">If someone registers as an individual, can they still join a team later?</h4>\r\n\r\nPre-registered individual participants can still become part of a team. Please <a href=\"/contact-us/\" alt=\"contact us\" title=\"contact us\">e-mail us</a> with the name of the team you would like to join or plan to create -- and we will make the necessary adjustments for you.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"do-i-have-to-register\">I plan to participate to support one of my friends and their team. Do I still have to register?</h4>\r\n\r\nIf you are walking, running or riding you must register to participate. If you plan to attend as a cheering section, you do not need to register. Registration is open the day of the event. \r\n\r\n<!--\r\n<h4 id=\"reg-forms\">Downloadable Registration Form</h4>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Reg-form-Race.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Brain Tumor Race - Registration Form</a><br>\r\n<a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Reg-form-Ride.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Brain Tumor Ride - Registration Form</a><br>\r\n<a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Reg-form-Walk.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Brain Tumor Walk - Registration Form</a><br>\r\n<!-- -->\r\n\r\n<h2>Donations</h2>\r\n<h4 id=\"funds\">Where do Brain Tumor Event funds go?</h4>\r\n\r\nProceeds from the event support research to find a cure for brain tumors, public policy advocacy, and patient information to make sure the critical needs of the brain tumor community are met, through the National Brain Tumor Society (NBTS). <a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/dollars-in-action/\" target=\"_blank\" alt=\"dollars in action\" title=\"dollars in action\">Learn more</a>.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"checks\">To whom do I make checks payable?</h4>\r\n\r\nAll checks can be made payable to the National Brain Tumor Society. If you wish to support a Walk participant, please complete <a href=\"http://www.braintumor.org/assets/docs/donate/4-allevents_14_doe_donationform_01-14-14.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" alt=\"support a walk participant\" title=\"support a walk participant\">this form</a> and send to:\r\n\r\nNational Brain Tumor Society\r\n[Event Name]\r\n55 Chapel Street, Suite 200\r\nNewton, MA 02458\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"matching-gifts\">What are Matching Gift Programs?</h4>\r\n\r\nMany employers have matching gift programs and will match any charitable contributions made by their employees. Ask your employer or HR department for more information. Generally, you will be asked to complete and submit a form to NBTS for approval. This form can be sent to the above address.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"tax-id\">What is the tax ID number for NBTS?</h4>\r\n\r\nThe NBTS Tax ID # (also referred to as EIN) is 04-3068130.\r\n\r\n<h2>Day of Event</h2> \r\n<h4 id=\"pets\">Are pets allowed at the event?</h4>\r\n\r\nPet policies vary, and are based on the rules of each venue. If pets are permitted at the venue, please keep your pets on a leash at all times. And, if your pet does not do well in large crowds, please consider leaving them at home. Please do not leave your pet in your car during the event. \r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"stroller\">Can I bring a stroller?</h4>\r\n\r\nYes, all walk routes are wheelchair and stroller accessible.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"emergency-management\">What emergency management procedures are in place for the event?</h4>\r\n\r\nThe safety and security of our event participants has always been a critical consideration in our event planning process, and we will continue to remain vigilant in this area.\r\n\r\nEvery National Brain Tumor Society Walk, Race, and Ride has an on-site security presence from set-up through the conclusion of the event. On-site security personnel have the responsibility to conduct multiple sweeps of the site to identify any potential risks, and respond accordingly. In addition to on-site security personnel, each National Brain Tumor Society Walk, Race and Ride is also equipped with a first aid tent, medical staff, and an ambulance.\r\n\r\n<h2>Contact Us</h2>\r\nIf you have a question we haven’t answered here, please <a href=\"/contact-us\" alt=\"\" title=\"\">contact us</a>!\r\n','Frequently Asked Questions','','publish','open','open','','frequently-asked-questions','','','2014-06-11 19:45:24','2014-06-11 19:45:24','',0,'http://events.braintumor.org/?page_id=197',0,'page','',0);
