INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2373,3,'2014-05-30 20:10:20','2014-05-30 20:10:20','<strong>SOLICIT DONATIONS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Donation Ask</strong>\r\nSubject line: Join me in the fight against brain tumors!\r\n\r\nI am taking part in the Dallas-Ft. Worth Brain Tumor Walk to support the fight against brain tumors. I am asking you to fight alongside me by making a donation to my team.  \r\n\r\nNational Brain Tumor Society is aggressively driving strategic research that will lead to therapies for adult and pediatric brain tumors. On a national level, National Brain Tumor Society advocates for public policy that meets the critical needs of the brain tumor community and also provides comprehensive information and resources. I believe in the National Brain Tumor Society - won’t you join me?\r\n \r\nThere are 700,000 people in the US living with a brain tumor. This year 69,000 more will be diagnosed. I walk for all of these people, and their caregivers, family, and friends who have been affected by their diagnosis. Please support my efforts and make a donation to this important cause.\r\n\r\nIt’s easy to make a gift online <link to your fundraising page> - or you can print a donation form to send a gift by mail.\r\n\r\nThank you for your consideration - your gift means so much!\r\n\r\n<strong>Donation Ask - Personal Story</strong>\r\nSubject line: Join me in the fight against brain tumors!\r\n\r\nI am taking part in the Dallas-Ft. Worth Brain Tumor Walk to support the fight against brain tumors. I am asking you to fight alongside me by making a donation to my team.  \r\n\r\n(Insert personal story here)\r\n\r\nThis is why your support would mean so very much to my team!\r\n\r\nNational Brain Tumor Society is aggressively driving strategic research that will lead to therapies for adult and pediatric brain tumors. On a national level, National Brain Tumor Society advocates for public policy that meets the critical needs of the brain tumor community and also provides comprehensive information and resources. I believe in the National Brain Tumor Society - won’t you join me by making a gift today?\r\n\r\nIt’s easy to make a gift online  <link to your fundraising page>  - or you can print a donation form to send a gift by mail.\r\n\r\nThank you for your consideration - your gift means so much to me!\r\n\r\n<strong>Follow up Donation Ask</strong>\r\nSubject line: Don’t forget to donate to help me fight against brain tumors!\r\n\r\nI have joined the National Brain Tumor Society in the fight against brain tumors because I believe they can drive the research, public policy, and resources needed for patients, families and caregivers.  \r\n\r\nI am taking action - but I can’t do it without your help. Recently you should have received a message from me asking for your support while I participate in the Dallas-Ft. Worth Brain Tumor Walk. I hope you will consider making a donation!\r\n\r\nDonate today-- visit my page to learn a little more about my team and our cause. <link to your fundraising page>\r\n\r\nYour donation means so much - not only to me, but for those living with the effects of a brain tumor and those that will be diagnosed. \r\n\r\nThank you!\r\n\r\n<strong>Donation Thank You</strong>\r\nSubject: Thank you for your donation\r\n\r\nThank you for your generous support of the Dallas-Ft. Worth Brain Tumor Walk. Your donation will benefit the National Brain Tumor Society and aid in the fight against brain tumors. \r\n\r\nYou should have received an email confirmation from the National Brain Tumor Society that contains your gift and tax information. If you have any questions, please call 866-455-3214.\r\n\r\n<strong>BUILD YOUR TEAM</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Recruit Virtual Walkers</strong>\r\nSubject line:  Walk with me - virtually!\r\n\r\nI recently accepted the challenge to participate in the Dallas-Ft. Worth Brain Tumor Walk. Right now, I’m asking my friends, family and coworkers to join my team and be by my side as we fight brain tumors. While miles, hours, or days might separate us, I know in my heart that you would be here with me if you could. So, I’m asking that you join my team - virtually!\r\n\r\nEven though you can’t be here in person, you can still join my team, support our efforts, and raise awareness by becoming a virtual participant. You will receive a personal web page and can fundraise using the online tools. All dollars raised by virtual participants are counted toward our team’s goal. \r\n\r\nWhy should you join from so far away?\r\n1. Because it’s easy!\r\n2. The National Brain Tumor Society is fiercely committed to finding a cure for brain tumors. \r\n3. I believe in the National Brain Tumor Society and their battle to fund the best research that will provide the therapies needed to put an end to brain tumors. \r\n\r\nPlease join me in this fight!\r\nThank you!\r\n\r\n<strong>Recruit Team Members</strong>\r\nSubject line: In search of a few good “teammates”\r\n\r\nI recently accepted the challenge to participate in the Dallas-Ft. Worth Brain Tumor Walk. I’d like to invite you to fight alongside me by joining my team!\r\n\r\nI need a dedicated team, comprised of people like you, to unite with me in the fight against brain tumors and support the National Brain Tumor Society’s work to find a cure. \r\n\r\nNational Brain Tumor Society is aggressively driving strategic research that will lead to therapies for adult and pediatric brain tumors. On a national level, National Brain Tumor Society advocates for public policy that meets the critical needs of the brain tumor community and also provides comprehensive information and resources. I believe in the National Brain Tumor Society - won’t you join me?\r\n \r\nThere are 700,000 people in the US living with a brain tumor. This year 210,000 more will be diagnosed. I walk for all of these people and their caregivers, family, and friends who have been affected by their diagnosis. Join my team and let’s have some fun while we support for this great cause! Register today!\r\n\r\nI can’t wait to have you as part of my team!\r\n\r\n<strong>Recruit Team Members - Personal Story</strong>\r\nSubject line: In search of a few good “teammates”\r\n\r\nI recently accepted the challenge to participate in the Dallas-Ft. Worth Brain Tumor Walk. I’d like to invite you to fight alongside me by joining my team!\r\n\r\nYou may already know why, but I want to share a little more about why this fight is so personal to me. \r\n(Insert personal story here)\r\n\r\nI need a dedicated team, comprised of people like you, to unite with me in the fight against brain tumors and support the National Brain Tumor Society’s work to find a cure. \r\n\r\nNational Brain Tumor Society is aggressively driving strategic research that will lead to therapies for adult and pediatric brain tumors. On a national level, National Brain Tumor Society advocates for public policy that meets the critical needs of the brain tumor community and also provides comprehensive information and resources. I believe in the National Brain Tumor Society - won’t you register today?\r\n\r\nI can’t wait to have you as part of my team!\r\n\r\n<strong>Welcome New Team Member</strong>\r\nSubject line: Welcome to my team!\r\n\r\nWelcome! I am so excited that you’ve joined my team. Together we are uniting to fight brain tumors and I couldn’t do it without you.\r\n\r\nWe have a lot of work to do. You may have noticed that you have been given your own personal web page. Please bookmark this page as you will be visiting it often! \r\n\r\nIf you need any other guidance check out the Help section, ask me, or the friendly staff at the National Brain Tumor Society. We are going to have a blast! I am thrilled to have you as part of my team and can’t wait to get started!\r\n\r\nTalk to you soon!\r\n\r\n<strong>Helpful Phrases</strong>\r\n\r\nWe have one month remaining until the event and have raised $XXXX, let\'s keep up the fundraising to continue the fight against brain tumors.\r\n\r\nWith less than XX weeks to go, how is your fundraising? Here are some fun tips to raise some money.','Fundraising Tips','','publish','closed','closed','','fundraising-tips','','','2014-05-30 20:10:20','2014-05-30 20:10:20','',1956,'http://events.braintumor.org/?post_type=events&#038;p=2373',0,'events','',0);
