tered participants unless they complete the process above.</i>\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"mailing-address\">When I register for the first time, should I use my home or work mailing address?</h4>\r\n\r\nParticipants should register using their home mailing address. This helps to eliminate confusion at registration and the chance of duplicate mailings.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"individual-and-team\">If someone registers as an individual, can they still join a team later?</h4>\r\n\r\nPre-registered individual participants can still become part of a team. Please <a href=\"/contact-us/\" alt=\"contact us\" title=\"contact us\">e-mail us</a> with the name of the team you would like to join or plan to create -- and we will make the necessary adjustments for you.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"do-i-have-to-register\">I plan to participate to support one of my friends and their team. Do I still have to register?</h4>\r\n\r\nIf you are walking, running or riding you must register to participate. If you plan to attend as a cheering section, you do not need to register. Registration is open the day of the event. \r\n\r\n<!--\r\n<h4 id=\"reg-forms\">Downloadable Registration Form</h4>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Reg-form-Race.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Brain Tumor Race - Registration Form</a><br>\r\n<a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Reg-form-Ride.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Brain Tumor Ride - Registration Form</a><br>\r\n<a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Reg-form-Walk.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Brain Tumor Walk - Registration Form</a><br>\r\n<!-- -->\r\n\r\n<h2>Donations</h2>\r\n<h4 id=\"funds\">Where do Brain Tumor Event funds go?</h4>\r\n\r\nProceeds from the event support research to find a cure for brain tumors, public policy advocacy, and patient information to make sure the critical needs of the brain tumor community are met, through the National Brain Tumor Society (NBTS). <a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/dollars-in-action/\" target=\"_blank\" alt=\"dollars in action\" title=\"dollars in action\">Learn more</a>.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"checks\">To whom do I make checks payable?</h4>\r\n\r\nAll checks can be made payable to the National Brain Tumor Society. If you wish to support a Walk participant, please complete <a href=\"http://www.braintumor.org/assets/docs/donate/4-allevents_14_doe_donationform_01-14-14.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" alt=\"support a walk participant\" title=\"support a walk participant\">this form</a> and send to:\r\n\r\nNational Brain Tumor Society\r\n[Event Name]\r\n55 Chapel Street, Suite 200\r\nNewton, MA 02458\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"matching-gifts\">What are Matching Gift Programs?</h4>\r\n\r\nMany employers have matching gift programs and will match any charitable contributions made by their employees. Ask your employer or HR department for more information. Generally, you will be asked to complete and submit a form to NBTS for approval. This form can be sent to the above address.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"tax-id\">What is the tax ID number for NBTS?</h4>\r\n\r\nThe NBTS Tax ID # (also referred to as EIN) is 04-3068130.\r\n\r\n<h2>Day of Event</h2> \r\n<h4 id=\"pets\">Are pets allowed at the event?</h4>\r\n\r\nPet policies vary, and are based on the rules of each venue. If pets are permitted at the venue, please keep your pets on a leash at all times. And, if your pet does not do well in large crowds, please consider leaving them at home. Please do not leave your pet in your car during the event. \r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"stroller\">Can I bring a stroller?</h4>\r\n\r\nYes, all walk routes are wheelchair and stroller accessible.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"emergency-management\">What emergency management procedures are in place for the event?</h4>\r\n\r\nThe safety and security of our event participants has always been a critical consideration in our event planning process, and we will continue to remain vigilant in this area.\r\n\r\nEvery National Brain Tumor Society Walk, Race, and Ride has an on-site security presence from set-up through the conclusion of the event. On-site security personnel have the responsibility to conduct multiple sweeps of the site to identify any potential risks, and respond accordingly. In addition to on-site security personnel, each National Brain Tumor Society Walk, Race and Ride is also equipped with a first aid tent, medical staff, and an ambulance.\r\n\r\n<h2>Contact Us</h2>\r\nIf you have a question we haven’t answered here, please <a href=\"/contact-us\" alt=\"\" title=\"\">contact us</a>!\r\n','Frequently Asked Questions','','inherit','open','open','','197-revision-v1','','','2014-06-11 19:45:24','2014-06-11 19:45:24','',197,'http://events.braintumor.org/197-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2442,6,'2014-06-11 19:52:31','2014-06-11 19:52:31','<div id=\"event_url\" style=\"display: none;\"></div>\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">// <![CDATA[\r\nif ($.cookie(\'event_cookie\')){\r\n  $(\'#event_url\').show();\r\n  $(\'#event_url\').html(\'<a href=\"\'+$.cookie(\'event_cookie\')+\'\"><strong>BACK TO EVENT</strong></a>\');\r\n};\r\n// ]]></script>\r\n<div class=\"jump-nav-container\">\r\n<ul class=\"jump-nav\">\r\n	<li><a href=\"#program\">Program</a></li>\r\n	<li class=\"jump-nav-spacer\">|</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#parking\">Directions &amp; Parking</a></li>\r\n	<li class=\"jump-nav-spacer\">|</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#faq\">FAQ</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>EVENT DETAILS</h3>\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> June 21, 2014\r\n<strong>Location:</strong> Randall’s Island Icahn Stadium\r\n<strong>Registration:</strong> 7:30 AM\r\n<strong>Program &amp; Activities:</strong> 5K walk Starts at 9:00 AM\r\n<strong>Length of Event:</strong> 5K Approx 3 miles\r\n<div id=\"incentives\">\r\n\r\n<strong>Event Incentives</strong>\r\n<strong>$1K Club Challenge</strong> – be entered to win an iPad mini® by giving or raising $1,000 by June 19\r\n<strong>Win signature gear</strong> – win National Brain Tumor Society gear by giving or raising $200 by June 20 at midnight.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"program\"><strong>Event Day Program</strong>\r\nTop team and top individual fundraisers will be acknowledged during the closing ceremony.Rain or shine the event will go on!Regardless of weather, layered clothing, wind-breakers, sunglasses, and sunscreen are recommended.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"parking\">\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions &amp; Parking</strong>\r\n20 Randall’s Park Island\r\nNew York, NY 10035\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/NBTS-Getting-to-Randall’s-Island.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> for directions by car, public transportation, and walking. There are several free parking lots near Icahn Stadium.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"enjoyment\">\r\n<strong>Enjoy Randall\'s Island Park!</strong>\r\nRandall’s Island Park is home to many fun places, including:\r\n	•	Miniature golf course\r\n	•	Batting cages\r\n	•	Nature trails\r\n	•	Beer gardens  \r\n	•	And much more!\r\n\r\nFor more information about fun things to do at Randall’s Island Park, please visit the <a href=\"http://www.randallsislandgolfcenter.com/\" target=\"_blank\">website.</a>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Site map</strong>\r\nComing Soon!\r\n<div id=\"vollunteer\"><strong>Volunteer Information</strong>\r\nInterested in volunteering for this event? Learn more about <a title=\"\" href=\"/events/new-york-brain-tumor-walk/volunteer-roles/\">volunteer opportunities</a>.\r\n<p>All funds raised through these events, allows the National Brain Tumor Society to advance research and public policy to improve the lives of all those living with a brain tumor, as well as anyone who will be diagnosed tomorrow. Our mission is to find a cure for brain tumors – <a href=\"/\">Search for your event and register today</a> to help make a difference in the fight against brain tumors.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"faq\"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong>\r\n<!-- LIST OF TOP 10 w/ANSWERS -->\r\n<a id=\"fee1\" href=\"#fee1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#fee\"><strong>Is there a registration fee?</strong></a>\r\n<div class=\"collapse\" id=\"fee\">There are no registration fees for a Brain Tumor Walk. However, you are required to register in order to participate in the walk and gain access to all event activities.Upon registration, you will receive a personal fundraising page and useful online tools to help you jumpstart your efforts. Even after the event is over, you will still have access to your personal fundraising page, allowing you to maximize your impact in the fight against brain tumors.</div>\r\n<a id=\"#min-amount1\" href=\"#min-amount1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#min-amount\"><strong>Am I required to fundraise a minimum amount?</strong></a>\r\n<div class=\"collapse\" id=\"min-amount\">Adults are encouraged to raise a minimum of $200 or more to help fund the discovery of a cure and better treatments for brain tumors.</div>\r\n<a id=\"#funds1\" href=\"#funds1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#funds\"><strong>Where do Brain Tumor Events funds go?</strong></a>\r\n<div class=\"collapse\" id=\"funds\">Proceeds from the event support research to find a cure for brain tumors, public policy advocacy, and patient information to make sure the critical needs of the brain tumor community are met, through the National Brain Tumor Society (NBTS).\r\n<a title=\"dollars in action\" href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/dollars-in-action/\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</div>\r\n<a id=\"#child1\" href=\"#child1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#child\"><strong>Do I need to register my children?</strong></a>\r\n<div class=\"collapse\" id=\"child\">Children ages 6-17 are required to register. Children ages 5 and under do not need to register for this event.</div>\r\n<a id=\"#team-reg1\" href=\"#team-reg1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#team-reg\"><strong>I plan to participate to support one of my friends and their team. Do I still have to register?</strong></a>\r\n<div class=\"collapse\" id=\"team-reg\">If you are walking, running or riding you must register to participate. If you plan to attend as a cheering section, you do not need to register. Registration is open the day of the event.</div>\r\n<a id=\"#volunteer1\" href=\"#volunteer1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#volunteer\"><strong>Can I walk and volunteer?</strong></a>\r\n<div class=\"collapse\" id=\"volunteer\">Yes! If you plan to walk and volunteer, please register as a Walker FIRST, and then <a title=\"contact us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">email your contact information to us</a>.</div>\r\n<a id=\"#gift1\" href=\"#gift1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#gift\"><strong>What are Matching Gift Programs?</strong></a>\r\n<div class=\"collapse\" id=\"gift\">Many employers have matching gift programs and will match any charitable contributions made by their employees. Ask your employer or HR department for more information. Generally, you will be asked to complete and submit a form to NBTS for approval. This form can be sent to the above address.</div>\r\n<a id=\"#checks1\" href=\"#checks1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#checks\"><strong>To whom do I make checks payable?</strong></a>\r\n<div class=\"collapse\" id=\"checks\">All checks can be made payable to the National Brain Tumor Society. If you wish to support a Walk participant, please complete <a title=\"support a walk participant\" href=\"http://www.braintumor.org/assets/docs/donate/4-allevents_14_doe_donationform_01-14-14.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">this form</a> and send to:National Brain Tumor Society\r\n[Event Name]\r\n55 Chapel Street, Suite 200\r\nNewton, MA 02458</div>\r\n<a id=\"#pets1\" href=\"#pets1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#pets\"><strong>Are pets allowed at the event?</strong></a>\r\n<div class=\"collapse\" id=\"pets\">Pet policies vary, and are based on the rules of each venue. If pets are permitted at the venue, please keep your pets on a leash at all times. And, if your pet does not do well in large crowds, please consider leaving them at home. Please do not leave your pet in your car during the event.</div>\r\n<a id=\"#t-shirt1\" href=\"#t-shirt1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#t-shirt\"><strong>Will I receive an event t-shirt?</strong></a>\r\n<div class=\"collapse\" id=\"t-shirt\">\r\n\r\nTo maximize every dollar raised, we only provide event T-shirts to registered survivors and volunteers. However, we also offer T-shirts for adults and children at each event, in exchange for a donation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<a title=\"View full FAQ document\" href=\"/frequently-asked-questions\">View full FAQ document</a>\r\n\r\n</div>','Event Details','','inherit','open','open','','98-revision-v1','','','2014-06-11 19:52:31','2014-06-11 19:52:31','',98,'http://events.braintumor.org/98-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2444,3,'2014-06-11 20:07:45','2014-06-11 20:07:45','Welcome to the <strong>Race for Hope Philadelphia</strong>, an event to raise awareness and much-needed resources to fund critical brain tumor-specific programs to improve the lives of all those affected by brain tumors. Hosted by the National Brain Tumor Society, the Race for Hope Philadelphia offers individuals and teams a chance to honor and remember loved ones, connect with others interested in the brain tumor cause, and helps to educate the local community on the diverse needs of the brain tumor community.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"View the full event details here\" href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/events/race-for-hope-philadelphia/event-details/\">View the full event details here</a>\r\n\r\nAll funds raised through our events allow the National Brain Tumor Society to advance research and public policy to improve the availability of new and better treatments, and fuel the discovery of a cure for brain tumors.','Race for Hope Philadelphia','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-v1','','','2014-06-11 20:07:45','2014-06-11 20:07:45','',55,'http://events.braintumor.org/55-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
