INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2595,7,'2014-07-04 00:20:22','2014-07-04 00:20:22','<div id=\"event_url\" style=\"display:none\"></div>\r\n<script>\r\n if ($.cookie(\'event_cookie\')){\r\n  $(\'#event_url\').show();\r\n  $(\'#event_url\').html(\'<a href=\"\'+$.cookie(\'event_cookie\')+\'\"><strong>BACK TO EVENT</strong></a>\');\r\n};\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"jump-nav-container\">\r\n	<ul class=\"jump-nav\">\r\n		<li><a href=\"#program\">Program</a></li>\r\n		<li class=\"jump-nav-spacer\">|</li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"#parking\">Directions & Parking</a></li>\r\n		<li class=\"jump-nav-spacer\">|</li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"#drop-off\">Drop Off</a></li>\r\n		<li class=\"jump-nav-spacer\">|</li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"#faq\">FAQ</a></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> Saturday, November 8, 2014\r\n<strong>Location:</strong> Trinity Park\r\n<strong>Registration:</strong> 8:00 AM - 9:00 AM\r\n<strong>Program &amp; Activities:</strong> 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM\r\n<strong>Length of Event:</strong> 5K Walk\r\n\r\n<div id=\"program\">\r\n<strong>Event Day Program</strong>\r\nRegistration: 8:00 AM – 9:00 AM\r\n\r\nAs a registered participant, you will receive a personal fundraising page and useful online tools to help jumpstart your efforts. Each participant is encouraged to raise a minimum of $200 or more to help fund the discovery of a cure and better treatments for brain tumors.\r\n\r\nPlease note: To maximize every dollar raised, National Brain Tumor Society only provides event T-shirts to registered survivors and volunteers. However, we also offer T-shirts for adults and children at each event, in exchange for a donation.\r\n\r\nWalk begins: 9:00 AM (approximately)\r\n\r\nThe 5K walk will start and finish at the balloon arch in Trinity Park. This is not a race and participants are not required to complete the full course. And, those who wish to remain onsite during the walk are welcome to do so. \r\n\r\nHelpful tips:\r\n\r\n* Please be sure to hydrate before and after the Walk.\r\n\r\n* Snacks and water will be provided to all participants after the Walk.\r\n\r\n* Don’t forget to wear weather appropriate clothing.  And be sure you have your sunglasses and sunscreen.\r\n\r\nRain or shine, the event will go on – and we look forward to seeing you! \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"help\" style=\"border:1px solid gray; padding:20px; margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\r\n	<strong>Need help getting started? <a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/k-participant-support/\" title=\"Participant Support\" target=\"_blank\">View our instructions and video tutorials</a>.</strong>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"parking\">\r\n<strong>Directions & Parking</strong>\r\nIf you are traveling to Trinity Park by car or public transportation and still want to map your travel online, please use the following street address:<br /><br />2100 River Drive, Ft. Worth, TX 76107\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?q=2100+River+Drive,+Ft.+Worth,+TX+76107&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hl=en&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=River+Dr,+Fort+Worth,+Tarrant,+Texas+76107&amp;z=14&amp;ll=32.744974,-97.351401&amp;output=embed\" height=\"300\" width=\"300\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe><br /><small><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-align: left;\" href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=embed&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=+Castle+Island,+Boston,+MA+&amp;aq=&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=43.307813,73.125&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=castle+island&amp;hnear=Castle+Island,+Boston,+Massachusetts+02127&amp;ll=42.337864,-71.011848&amp;spn=0.019033,0.025749&amp;z=14\">View Larger Map</a></small>\r\n\r\nParking at the site is limited, and will be available on a first come first served basis. Additionally, free public parking will be available at the Billingsley Field House parking lot (1355 Foch St., Ft. Worth, TX). Lot needs to be cleared by Noon.\r\n\r\nA complimentary shuttle will run continuously from 8:00 AM until 12:00 PM between Billingsley Field House and the meeting site.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"drop-off\">\r\n<strong>Drop Off</strong>\r\nComing Soon!\r\n</div>\r\n<br/>\r\n<div id=\"vollunteer\">\r\n<strong>Volunteer Information</strong>\r\nInterested in volunteering for this event? Learn more about <a href=\"/events/dallas-ft-worth-brain-tumor-walk-kimbia/volunteer-roles/\" alt=\"volunteer opportunities\" title=\"volunteer opportunities\">volunteer opportunities</a>\r\n\r\nAll funds raised through these events, allows the National Brain Tumor Society to advance research and public policy to improve the lives of all those living with a brain tumor, as well as anyone who will be diagnosed tomorrow. Our mission is to find a cure for brain tumors – <a href=\"/\">Search for your event and register today</a> to help make a difference in the fight against brain tumors.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- Site Map -->\r\n<div id=\"site-map\">\r\n<strong>Site Map</strong>\r\nComing Soon!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"faq\">\r\n<strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong>\r\n<!-- LIST OF TOP 10 w/ANSWERS -->\r\n<a href=\"#fee1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#fee\" id=\"fee1\"><strong>Is there a registration fee?</strong></a><br />\r\n<div id=\"fee\" class=\"collapse\">There are no registration fees for a Brain Tumor Walk. However, you are required to register in order to participate in the walk and gain access to all event activities. \r\n\r\nUpon registration, you will receive a personal fundraising page and useful online tools to help you jumpstart your efforts. Even after the event is over, you will still have access to your personal fundraising page, allowing you to maximize your impact in the fight against brain tumors.</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#min-amount1\" id=\"#min-amount1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#min-amount\"><strong>Am I required to fundraise a minimum amount?</strong></a><br />\r\n<div id=\"min-amount\" class=\"collapse\">Adults are encouraged to raise a minimum of $200 or more to help fund the discovery of a cure and better treatments for brain tumors.</div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#funds1\" id=\"#funds1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#funds\"><strong>Where do Brain Tumor Events funds go?</strong></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<div id=\"funds\" class=\"collapse\">Proceeds from the event support research to find a cure for brain tumors, public policy advocacy, and patient information to make sure the critical needs of the brain tumor community are met, through the National Brain Tumor Society (NBTS). \r\n<a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/dollars-in-action/\" target=\"_blank\" alt=\"dollars in action\" title=\"dollars in action\">Learn more</a>.</div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#child1\" id=\"#child1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#child\"><strong>Do I need to register my children?</strong></a><br />\r\n<div id=\"child\" class=\"collapse\">Children ages 6-17 are required to register. Children ages 5 and under do not need to register for this event.</div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#team-reg1\" id=\"#team-reg1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#team-reg\"><strong>I plan to participate to support one of my friends and their team. Do I still have to register?</strong></a>\r\n<div id=\"team-reg\" class=\"collapse\">If you are walking, running or riding you must register to participate. If you plan to attend as a cheering section, you do not need to register. Registration is open the day of the event. </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#volunteer1\" id=\"#volunteer1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#volunteer\"><strong>Can I walk and volunteer?</strong></a><br />\r\n<div id=\"volunteer\" class=\"collapse\">Yes! If you plan to walk and volunteer, please register as a Walker FIRST, and then <a href=\"/contact-us/\" alt=\"contact us\" title=\"contact us\">email your contact information to us</a>.</div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#gift1\" id=\"#gift1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#gift\"><strong>What are Matching Gift Programs?</strong></a><br />\r\n<div id=\"gift\" class=\"collapse\">Many employers have matching gift programs and will match any charitable contributions made by their employees. Ask your employer or HR department for more information. Generally, you will be asked to complete and submit a form to NBTS for approval. This form can be sent to the above address.</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#checks1\" id=\"#checks1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#checks\"><strong>To whom do I make checks payable?</strong></a><br />\r\n<div id=\"checks\" class=\"collapse\">All checks can be made payable to the National Brain Tumor Society. If you wish to support a Walk participant, please complete <a href=\"http://www.braintumor.org/assets/docs/donate/4-allevents_14_doe_donationform_01-14-14.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" alt=\"support a walk participant\" title=\"support a walk participant\">this form</a> and send to:</p>\r\n<p>National Brain Tumor Society<br />\r\n[Event Name]<br />\r\n55 Chapel Street, Suite 200<br />\r\nNewton, MA 02458</div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#pets1\" id=\"#pets1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#pets\"><strong>Are pets allowed at the event?</strong></a><br />\r\n<div id=\"pets\" class=\"collapse\">Pet policies vary, and are based on the rules of each venue. If pets are permitted at the venue, please keep your pets on a leash at all times. And, if your pet does not do well in large crowds, please consider leaving them at home. Please do not leave your pet in your car during the event.</div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"#t-shirt1\" id=\"#t-shirt1\" data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-target=\"#t-shirt\"><strong>Will I receive an event t-shirt?</strong></a><br/>\r\n<div id=\"t-shirt\" class=\"collapse\"><p>To maximize every dollar raised, we only provide event T-shirts to registered survivors and volunteers. However, we also offer T-shirts for adults and children at each event, in exchange for a donation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"/frequently-asked-questions\" alt=\"View full FAQ document\" title=\"View full FAQ document\">View full FAQ document</a>\r\n</div>','Event Details','','inherit','open','open','','1958-revision-v1','','','2014-07-04 00:20:22','2014-07-04 00:20:22','',1958,'http://events.braintumor.org/1958-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2596,7,'2014-07-04 00:20:35','2014-07-04 00:20:35','<div class=\"widget\">\r\n<script src=\'https://widgets.kimbia.com/widgets/status.js?id=47J6729\'></script>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nWelcome to the <strong>Dallas-Ft. Worth Brain Tumor Walk</strong>, an event to raise awareness and much-needed resources to fund critical brain tumor-specific programs to improve the lives of all those affected by brain tumors. Hosted by the National Brain Tumor Society, the Dallas-Ft. Worth Brain Tumor Walk offers individuals and teams a chance to honor and remember loved ones, connect with others interested in the brain tumor cause, and helps to educate the local community on the diverse needs of the brain tumor community.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"View the full event details here\" href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/events/dallas-ft-worth-brain-tumor-walk/event-details/\">View the full event details here</a>\r\n\r\nAll funds raised through our events allow the National Brain Tumor Society to advance research and public policy to improve the availability of new and better treatments, and fuel the discovery of a cure for brain tumors.\r\n\r\n<div id=\"help\" style=\"border:1px solid gray; padding:20px; margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\r\n	<strong>Need help getting started? <a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/k-participant-support/\" title=\"Participant Support\" target=\"_blank\">View our instructions and video tutorials</a>.</strong>\r\n</div>','Dallas-Ft. Worth Brain Tumor Walk','','inherit','open','open','','1956-revision-v1','','','2014-07-04 00:20:35','2014-07-04 00:20:35','',1956,'http://events.braintumor.org/1956-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2597,7,'2014-07-04 00:20:47','2014-07-04 00:20:47','<script src=\'https://widgets.kimbia.com/widgets/status.js?id=2JKAX61\'></script>\r\n\r\nWelcome to the <strong>Long Island Brain Tumor Walk</strong>, an event to raise awareness and much-needed resources to fund critical brain tumor-specific programs to improve the lives of all those affected by brain tumors. Hosted by the National Brain Tumor Society, the Long Island Brain Tumor Walk offers individuals and teams a chance to honor and remember loved ones, connect with others interested in the brain tumor cause, and helps to educate the local community on the diverse needs of the brain tumor community.\r\n\r\nAll funds raised through our events allow the National Brain Tumor Society to advance research and public policy to improve the availability of new and better treatments, and fuel the discovery of a cure for brain tumors.\r\n\r\n<div id=\"help\" style=\"border:1px solid gray; padding:20px; margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\r\n	<strong>Need help getting started? <a href=\"http://events.braintumor.org/k-participant-support/\" title=\"Participant Support\" target=\"_blank\">View our instructions and video tutorials</a>.</strong>\r\n</div>','Long Island Brain Tumor Walk','','inherit','open','open','','2339-revision-v1','','','2014-07-04 00:20:47','2014-07-04 00:20:47','',2339,'http://events.braintumor.org/2339-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2598,7,'2014-07-04 15:43:12','2014-07-04 15:43:12','<h3>Watch a video</h3>\n<em>For full-screen viewing (recommended) click the \"Go Full Screen\" button in the video below:</em> <img src=\"http://www.braintumorcommunity.org/images/brightcove_single_player_fullscreen_button.png\">\n\n<div style=\"padding-left:20px\">\n	<!-- Start of Brightcove Player -->\n\n	<div style=\"display:none\">\n\n	</div>\n\n	<!--\n	By use of this code snippet, I agree to the Brightcove Publisher T and C \n	found at https://accounts.brightcove.com/en/terms-and-conditions/. \n	-->\n\n	<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://admin.brightcove.com/js/BrightcoveExperiences.js\"></script>\n\n	<object id=\"myExperience3658200979001\" class=\"BrightcoveExperience\">\n	  <param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#FFFFFF\" />\n	  <param name=\"width\" value=\"486\" />\n	  <param name=\"height\" value=\"412\" />\n	  <param name=\"playerID\" value=\"1280417223001\" />\n	  <param name=\"playerKey\" value=\"AQ~~,AAABKaXpDek~,QOj2HMaUjMXGzswHGEkjRelzugFfiPTf\" />\n	  <param name=\"isVid\" value=\"true\" />\n	  <param name=\"dynamicStreaming\" value=\"true\" />\n	    \n	  <param name=\"@videoPlayer\" value=\"3658200979001\" />\n	</object>\n\n	<!-- \n	This script tag will cause the Brightcove Players defined above it to be created as soon\n	as the line is read by the browser. If you wish to have the player instantiated only after\n	the rest of the HTML is processed and the page load is complete, remove the line.\n	-->\n	<script type=\"text/javascript\">brightcove.createExperiences();</script>\n\n	<!-- End of Brightcove Player -->\n</div>\n\n<h3>Download text instructions</h3>\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"http://www.braintumorcommunity.org/Guides/How_to_create_a_team_during_registration-a.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">How to create a team during registration</a> (PDF)</li></ul>\n\n<h3>View text instructions</h3>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Visit events.braintumor.org/events-list/ to find the event you\'d like to register for. Follow the link to your event\'s website and click the \"REGISTER TO RACE\" button.\nNote that there\'s a separate button for signing up as a volunteer. That signup process is very similar to this one but to register as a volunteer you must click the \"SIGN UP TO VOLUNTEER\" button.</li>\n<li>If you have an account already you can sign in to the left. Otherwise, click \"CREATE NEW ACCOUNT\" to create an account in our system or click \"Log In with Facebook\" to register using your Facebook account.</li>\n<li>Click \"CREATE A TEAM\" to begin setting up your team.</li>\n<li>Choose the appropriate registration type (Runner, Walker, etc.).</li>\n<li>Enter your team\'s name in the \"Team Name\" field.</li>\n<li>You can use the \"Team Description\" field to explain why you\'re participating in this event and why you\'re creating a team. This is useful information for prospective donors and teammates.</li>\n<li>The default team fundraising goal is $500 but you\'re encouraged to increase the goal to the amount you\'d like to shoot for in the \"Team Fundraising Goal\" field.</li>\n<li>You\'ll notice some permission questions that determine whether the public can see your team. It\'s recommended that these options are left checked so that people can find your team and donate or join.</li>\n<li>Review and agree to the waiver in the \"ADDITIONAL QUESTIONS\" section (this is a standard waiver that\'s used for all National Brain Tumor Society events and participants), then click \"NEXT\".</li>\n<li>Now that you\'ve entered your team information it\'s time to complete your registration as a fundraiser. This is the same process your team members will go through when they register.</li>\n<li>Enter your name, address, phone number, and email address. Be sure to enter a valid phone number and email address in case we need to contact you.</li>\n<li>Enter emergency contact information.</li>\n<li>Create a username and password so that you can log into the site in the future to manage your fundraising efforts, email your team, and recruit team members.</li>\n<li>Click NEXT to move on to the final stage of this process.</li>\n<li>You\'re encouraged to adjust your personal fundraising goal here. Your personal fundraising efforts work toward the team fundraising goal you set earlier, so decide how much of the team goal you\'d like to undertake as an individual fundraiser.</li>\n<li>You can start your fundraising efforts right now by adding a donation in the \"DONATION\" field. This initial gift helps you move toward your goal and can be helpful when asking people to donate as it\'s encouraging for them to see existing donations.</li>\n<li>You\'ll see another \"PERMISSION QUESTIONS\" section here. This is the same set of permissions you saw on the team page except these are for your personal page.</li>\n<li>The \"Display Name\" field allows you to enter something other than your real name to display on your fundraising page.</li>\n<li>Enter your birthdate in the \"Date of Birth\" field by first choosing a month, then a year, then a day (it has to be done in that order) in the pop-up menu.</li>\n<li>Choose your gender.</li>\n<li>If you\'re a brain tumor survivor or a volunteer, choose your T-shirt size (unique T-shirts are provided to Volunteers and brain tumor survivors).</li>\n<li>Specify your connection to brain tumors (patient/survivor, family, friend, etc).</li>\n<li>If someone recruited you for this event please specify his or her name in the field labeled \"Please list the first and last name…\"</li>\n<li>Review and agree to another standard waiver. This is the same waiver you agreed to earlier but this one is for you as an individual rather than for your team.</li>\n<li>If you have any family or friends to register you can click the blue \"ADD OTHERS\" button below the waiver.</li>\n<li>Click NEXT and you\'ll see the final step, which is to verify your contact information. If anything needs to be fixed click \"PREVIOUS\" and correct the errors. If everything looks correct click \"REGISTER ME\" to complete your registration.</li>\n<li>That\'s it. Your registration is complete and your team has been created. You\'ll receive a confirmation email with a link to your personal page.</li>\n<li>You\'ll be presented with an opportunity to start fundraising right away by emailing people you know and asking for donations. You can also connect with Facebook by scrolling down to the GET SOCIAL section and clicking \"GET STARTED\". If you\'d like to skip the items on this page for now you can click \"SKIP THIS STEP\" and you\'ll be brought to your Participant Center, where you can click \"TEAM\" to manage and recruit for your team; \"FUNDRAISING\" to start asking for donations; or \"PROFILE\" to edit your personal profile. Keep an eye out for Participant Center help documentation and videos on your event\'s website</li>\n</ol>\n\n<div style=\"border:1px solid gray; padding-left:20px;\">\n	<p><strong>If you need help...</strong></p>\n\n	<p>Please contact us if you need assistance. We\'re here to help!</p>\n\n	<p><a href=\"mailto:donations@braintumor.org\">donations@braintumor.org</a><br />\n	866-455-3214</p>\n</div>','Participant Support: How to create a team during registration','','inherit','open','open','','2522-autosave-v1','','','2014-07-04 15:43:12','2014-07-04 15:43:12','',2522,'http://events.braintumor.org/2522-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
